18-game National Basketball Association losing streak with a
91-81 road victory over the  Chicago  Bulls.  Kemba Walker  scored 18 points to lead the Bobcats, who
outscored the Bulls 26-16 during the fourth quarter yesterday at
the United Center in Chicago.  It was Charlotteâ€™s first win since Nov. 24 against the
Washington and helped the Bobcats (8-23) surpass their win total
from their 7-59 campaign in 2011-12.  The Brooklyn Nets yesterday lost their first game since
